  "bio_raw": "Dewan Ahmed Muhtasim is an academic and researcher specializing in artificial intelligence, machine learning, computer vision, and neural networks. He received his B.Sc. in Computer Science (2020) and Master of Computing (Full Research Mode) in Artificial Intelligence (2024) from University Kebangsaan Malaysia (UKM), where his research focused on generative adversarial networks (GANs) for facial inpainting. Currently, he is a Lecturer in the Department of Computer Science and Engineering at the University of Liberal Arts Bangladesh (ULAB), teaching and mentoring students in machine learning and AI.\nHis professional background includes serving as a Lecturer at Metropolitan University, Bangladesh, a Research Assistant at the Centre for Artificial Intelligence Technology (CAIT), UKM, and a Full-Stack Web Developer at Magik Tech Sdn Bhd in Malaysia. With more than 12 research publications in top peer-reviewed international journals and contributions to projects such as a facial liveness detection system, he aims to advance innovation and critical thinking in academia and research.",
  "stated_interests": [
    "Machine Learning, Artificial Intelligence, Image Processing, Data Science Computer Vision."
  ],
  "education": [
    {
      "raw": "Education\nMSc in Computer  Science\n(Full Research), Centre for Artificial Intelligence and Technology (CAIT), University Kebangsaan Malaysia (UKM), March 2024, Thesis: High-Frequency Patch-Based Generative Adversarial Network (HF-PGAN): A Face Inpainting Network for Large Missing Regions in Virtual Reality Scenario.\nBSc, Faculty of Information Science and Technology\n, University Kebangsaan Malaysia (UKM), August 2020"
    }
  ],
